        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="15">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9512071">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                for Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open engine cover and locate engine throttle lever (Item 3) and transmission modulator
                    cable slide lever (Item 6) at engine fuel injection pump (Item 4), near the oil pipe on the left
                    side of the engine.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9512071" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512071.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512072">Figure 2</hotlnk>
                    for Items in parentheses.
                </para>
                <para>Remove both accelerator throttle return springs (Item 1) from the roller bolt rollers (Item 2).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9512072" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512072.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the accelerator rod (Item 3) from the ball stud at each end and set aside.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove accelerator pedal rod ball stud (Item 4) from the engine throttle break-over
                    lever and engine throttle lever (Items 5 and 6) by removing the hex lock nut and flat washer. Set
                    aside for reuse during assembly. Place accelerator pedal rod end out of the way at the pedal end.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove modulator cable slide lever (Item 7) from the engine throttle lever (Item 6) by
                    removing the shoulder bolt, flat washer and self-locking nut (Items 8 and 9). Place the modulator
                    cable slide lever out of the way.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512073">Figure 3</hotlnk>
                    for Items in parentheses.
                </para>
                <para>Remove engine throttle lever (Item 2) with roller bolt assembly (Item 4) from engine throttle
                    break-over lever (Item 1).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9512073" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512073.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove engine throttle break-over lever (Item 1) by loosening the pinch bolt being
                    careful not to disturb the pinch bolt spacer.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512074">Figure 4</hotlnk>
                    for Items in parentheses.
                </para>
                <para>Remove "C" ring retaining clips (Item 1) from both ends of the roller bolt (Item 2) and remove the
                    rollers (Item 3). Set aside the rollers and "C" ring retaining clips to reuse during assembly.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9512074" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512074.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove flanged hex nut (Item 4) from one side of roller bolt (Item 2) and remove roller
                    bolt from engine throttle lever (Item 5). Set aside the flanged hex nut to reuse during assembly,
                    and discard the roller bolt and engine throttle lever.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512075">Figure 5.</hotlnk>
                </para>
                <para>Discard old bracket and bolt (shown on left). New bolt and bracket are shown on the right.</para>
                <figure id="f9512075" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512075.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512076">Figure 6</hotlnk>
                    for Items in parentheses.
                </para>
                <para>Install new roller bolt (Item 1) on new engine throttle lever bracket (Item 2); secure with flange
                    hex nut (Item 3) removed in step 9. Tighten to 22 ft-lbs. (29.83 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9512076" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512076.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install rollers (Item 4) removed in step 8 on new roller bolt (Item 1). Secure with "C"
                    ring retaining clips (Item 5) removed in step 8.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512077">Figure 7.</hotlnk>
                </para>
                <para></para>
                <figure id="f9512077" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512077.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512078">Figure 8.</hotlnk>
                </para>
                <para>Install engine throttle break-over lever on throttle shaft. Dimension from electric shutoff
                    mounting flange to accelerator pedal rod ball stud hole is 16-1/2" with throttle shaft in idle
                    position. Tighten the engine throttle break-over lever clamping bolt making sure that the pinch bolt
                    spacer is located between the two ears of the engine throttle break-over lever.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9512078" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512078.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512079">Figure 9</hotlnk>
                    for Items in parentheses.
                </para>
                <para>Install new engine throttle lever bracket and roller bolt assembly (Items 1 and 2) on the engine
                    throttle break-over lever (Item 3,) and secure with 5/16 hex bolt, lock washer, hex nut (Item 4) and
                    1/4 hex bolt, lock washer, hex nut (Item 5).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9512079" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512079.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f951207a">Figure 10</hotlnk>
                    for Items in parentheses.
                </para>
                <para>Install both accelerator throttle return springs (Item 5) onto the roller bolt rollers (Item 6).
                </para>
                <figure id="f951207a" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G951207A.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f951207b">Figure 11.</hotlnk>
                </para>
                <para>Insert accelerator rod ball stud in mounting holes as shown and secure with flat washers and hex
                    lock nut.
                </para>
                <figure id="f951207b" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G951207B.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f951207c">Figure 12.</hotlnk>
                </para>
                <para>Install new 1/4" flat washer onto the roller bolt rod, then install modulator cable slide lever
                    and second new 1/4" flat washer, then install new 1/16" roller pin.
                </para>
                <figure id="f951207c" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G951207C.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 12.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f951207d">Figure 13</hotlnk>
                    for Items in parentheses.
                </para>
                <para>Loosen jam nuts (Item 1) on the accelerator pedal rod (Item 2). With injection pump in idle
                    position and with accelerator pedal held in idle position, adjust accelerator rod ends equally until
                    accelerator rod ends will snap onto both ball studs.
                </para>
                <figure id="f951207d" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G951207D.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 13.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f951207e">Figure 14</hotlnk>
                    for Items in parentheses.
                </para>
                <para>Adjust transmission modulator cable (Item 1) at modulator cable slide lever (Item 2) as follows:
                </para>
                <figure id="f951207e" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G951207E.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 14.</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Adjust the modulator cable slide lever with the engine off.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen and move both jam nuts (Item 3) away from the modulator cable slide lever
                        (Item 2).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Push, by hand, the engine throttle break-over lever (Item 4) forward to engine
                        break-over spring feature (full throttle), and hold in position.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Pull the modulator cable threaded end (Item 5) through the hole in the modulator
                        cable slide lever (Item 2) until full cable travel is obtained.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Run both jam nuts (Item 3) up against the slide lever (Item 2) and tighten to 80-110
                        in-lbs. (9-12 N&#8226;m).
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f951207f">Figure 15</hotlnk>
                    for Items in parentheses.
                </para>
                <para>Adjust accelerator pedal stop bolt (Item 1) to new higher pedal position by loosening jam nut
                    (Item 2) and adjusting the stop bolt up to an approximate height of 2.7 inches from the bus floor to
                    the top of the stop bolt. Final adjust the stop bolt so there is 1/4 inch clearance between the stop
                    bolt and the pedal when the accelerator is at full throttle, without override in the break-over
                    lever. This should translate to approximately 1/8 inch override in the break-over lever when the
                    pedal is in contact with the stop bolt.
                </para>
                <figure id="f951207f" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G951207F.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 15.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">All joints must work freely. Check for interference and binding. Do not lubricate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Road test before returning vehicle to service.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
